WEBVTT

00:08.970 --> 00:11.737
Could I have everybody's
attention, please?

00:11.772 --> 00:12.738
To the bride and groom.

00:14.675 --> 00:15.941
Whoa, whoa, wait, wait.

00:15.977 --> 00:17.221
One more time,
I missed it there, Clark.

00:19.013 --> 00:21.547
For Hodgins.
To the bride and groom!

00:24.552 --> 00:27.586
♪ One crazy night in Frisco ♪

00:27.622 --> 00:31.123
♪ There with Diamond Disco ♪

00:31.158 --> 00:32.725
♪ Oh, we were comin' undone ♪

00:32.759 --> 00:35.194
♪ Just havin' the time
of our life... ♪

00:35.229 --> 00:36.428
Wait, wait, wait.

00:36.464 --> 00:39.131
Whoa, whoa.
Whoa! Careful, Dr. Saroyan.

00:39.166 --> 00:41.000
Don't hurt yourself.
Or anyone else.

00:41.035 --> 00:43.369
Don't forget, I am still
technically your boss, Clark.

00:43.404 --> 00:45.304
At least until next week.
Oh, that's right.

00:45.339 --> 00:47.517
- When do you leave on your big trip?
- First thing Friday morning.

00:47.541 --> 00:49.375
I still can't believe
you got Cam to leave

00:49.410 --> 00:50.876
for six months.

00:50.911 --> 00:52.311
Well, it's been eight years

00:52.346 --> 00:53.763
since I've had a vacation--
I was overdue.

00:53.787 --> 00:55.620
Before we let Arastoo
get away,

00:55.656 --> 00:58.156
let's take an interns picture.

00:58.192 --> 00:59.891
Daisy, none of us
are interns anymore.

00:59.927 --> 01:00.840
Oh, there's Angela.

01:00.864 --> 01:03.764
Whoa!
My bad. My bad.

01:03.864 --> 01:04.864
Cam. Cam?

01:04.897 --> 01:06.932
I'll be back, babe.

01:06.967 --> 01:08.266
Maybe you can help.

01:08.302 --> 01:10.535
There's a gift
without a card.

01:10.571 --> 01:11.681
The problem is, I don't know how

01:11.705 --> 01:13.839
to categorize it
on my spreadsheet.

01:13.874 --> 01:15.941
Don't worry about it.
Just have fun.

01:15.976 --> 01:18.443
Oh, look at me.
I am.

01:18.479 --> 01:20.245
Then I will leave you to it.

01:20.280 --> 01:22.414
Oh, uh,
thank you again

01:22.449 --> 01:25.283
for taking care of everything
for Zack's hearing tomorrow.

01:25.319 --> 01:26.718
Dr. Hodgins and I
have it covered.

01:26.753 --> 01:28.954
Besides, we have to get used

01:28.989 --> 01:30.288
to solving cases without you.

01:30.324 --> 01:32.757
I was gonna wait
until tomorrow to tell you,

01:32.793 --> 01:35.727
but who knows, maybe the drinks
are getting to me...

01:35.762 --> 01:38.630
Anyway, um, I'm considering
handing over my role

01:38.665 --> 01:42.767
as administrative head
of the Jeffersonian.

01:42.803 --> 01:44.870
Truth is, I don't know
where the next chapter

01:44.905 --> 01:46.571
of my life's gonna
take me, so...

01:46.607 --> 01:48.707
If you do decide
to find a replacement,

01:48.742 --> 01:49.908
I think we both know

01:49.943 --> 01:52.611
who the obvious
choice would be.

01:52.646 --> 01:54.079
I agree.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.458
Anyway, we don't need
to talk about this now.

01:55.482 --> 01:57.349
I just... it's something
to think about.

01:57.384 --> 01:59.651
And just so you know,

01:59.686 --> 02:00.930
Christine's trying to give
Michael Vincent a wet willy.

02:00.954 --> 02:02.120
Oh, Christine!

02:02.155 --> 02:04.422
You could perforate
his eardrum.

02:04.458 --> 02:06.791
Cam, it's time.
No, no, no, Felicia.

02:06.827 --> 02:08.158
I told you no bouquet toss.

02:08.195 --> 02:10.195
The number of weddings
where I've almost been

02:10.229 --> 02:11.608
knocked out by
overzealous bridesmaids... No!

02:11.632 --> 02:13.431
Move out of the way,
ladies.

02:17.671 --> 02:19.504
This bouquet is mine.

02:20.607 --> 02:23.074
Okay, here I go.
Is everyone ready?

02:23.110 --> 02:24.509
Throw it now.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.946
Okay, one,

02:27.981 --> 02:31.116
two...

02:31.151 --> 02:32.651
♪ Out all night, it's 4:00 ♪

02:32.686 --> 02:34.152
♪ We don't care,
we never stop... ♪

02:34.187 --> 02:36.521
Dr. Saroyan,
can I wear your veil?

02:36.557 --> 02:39.057
Of course you can,
sweetie.

02:39.092 --> 02:40.625
♪ Always true to who we are ♪

02:40.661 --> 02:42.661
♪ We don't care, we never stop ♪

02:42.696 --> 02:44.563
♪ We won't be something
we're not ♪

02:44.598 --> 02:46.631
♪ We don't care, we never stop ♪
Okay.

02:46.667 --> 02:48.500
There you go.
Thank you.

02:48.535 --> 02:50.602
♪ We never stop, we never stop ♪

02:54.374 --> 02:57.342
Hey.
You okay?

02:57.377 --> 02:59.678
Oh, yeah, I'm great.
It's nothing.

02:59.713 --> 03:01.157
What's important is
that you're happy.

03:01.181 --> 03:03.548
- I am.
- Arastoo's a great guy.

03:03.584 --> 03:05.884
If we are half as happy
as you and Brennan,

03:05.919 --> 03:07.485
I will consider it
a success.

03:07.521 --> 03:10.322
Okay, I think I'm probably
one too many drinks in

03:10.357 --> 03:11.436
to be holding a child.

03:11.460 --> 03:13.025
Oh, yeah, that's
really comforting.

03:13.026 --> 03:14.960
Man!
Real comforting, Aubrey.

03:14.995 --> 03:15.776
To the bar.

03:15.800 --> 03:17.626
Okay, but he's gonna hurt
in the morning, huh?

03:18.165 --> 03:19.464
You want to go find Mom?
I'll see you soon.

03:19.488 --> 03:20.399
Okay.

03:20.400 --> 03:21.633
Come on, let's go, buddy.

03:21.668 --> 03:23.134
Mrs. Vaziri?

03:23.170 --> 03:24.859
I'm actually not
changing my name.

03:24.883 --> 03:25.571
Oh, so sorry.

03:25.572 --> 03:27.350
I just wanted to inform you
we've moved your personal items

03:27.374 --> 03:29.341
from the changing area
into your car.

03:29.376 --> 03:31.576
Oh, thank you very much.

03:35.215 --> 03:36.581
Hello.

03:36.617 --> 03:40.752
Hi. Yes, I, uh, I'd like
to say a couple words.

03:42.489 --> 03:46.825
So, as most of you know,
I'm Cam's daughter.

03:46.860 --> 03:50.295
Which means I know better
than anyone

03:50.330 --> 03:54.366
that my mom can be stubborn,
to say the least.

03:56.770 --> 04:00.171
So she's not easily
swept off of her feet.

04:00.207 --> 04:01.906
But when it came to Arastoo,

04:01.942 --> 04:04.376
it was clear immediately

04:04.411 --> 04:05.910
that she was meant
to be with him.

04:05.946 --> 04:08.947
And even she couldn't deny it.

04:08.982 --> 04:12.951
So, Mom, Arastoo,

04:12.986 --> 04:16.321
I love you both so much.

04:18.225 --> 04:21.826
And I wish you a long
and happy marriage.

04:21.862 --> 04:25.930
Cheers.

04:26.967 --> 04:31.069
And without further ado,

04:31.104 --> 04:33.138
I'd like to invite
the happy couple

04:33.173 --> 04:34.906
onto the dance floor.

04:38.278 --> 04:40.945
Ow!

04:47.421 --> 04:51.956
♪ When I look in your eyes ♪

04:51.992 --> 04:55.694
♪ That's when I realize ♪

04:55.729 --> 04:58.430
♪ I'd be nothing ♪

04:58.465 --> 05:02.500
♪ Nothing without you ♪

05:02.536 --> 05:07.405
♪ Like the bird in the sky ♪

05:07.441 --> 05:10.909
♪ I need you so I can fly ♪

05:10.944 --> 05:14.379
♪ 'Cause I'm nothing ♪

05:14.414 --> 05:18.016
♪ I'm nothing without you ♪

05:19.686 --> 05:24.322
♪ Like a river that flows
to the sea ♪

05:24.357 --> 05:28.093
♪ Without you there's no me ♪

05:28.128 --> 05:31.029
♪ In my heart... ♪

05:31.064 --> 05:32.831
Arastoo?

05:34.534 --> 05:36.735
Good morning,
sleepyhead.

05:36.770 --> 05:38.570
Good morning.

05:38.605 --> 05:40.338
Ah, thank you.

05:40.373 --> 05:41.906
What time is it?

05:41.942 --> 05:43.074
11:00.

05:43.110 --> 05:44.509
11:00? I have to...

05:44.544 --> 05:46.644
No.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.812
I have to do nothing?

05:47.848 --> 05:49.981
Wow. This is nice.

05:50.016 --> 05:52.584
Not a bad way
to start our new life.

05:52.619 --> 05:55.053
To sleeping in.

05:55.922 --> 05:57.522
Mmm...

05:57.557 --> 05:58.568
Uh-uh-uh!
What are you doing?

05:58.592 --> 05:59.724
I am not working.

05:59.760 --> 06:01.659
I am just checking
on Michelle.

06:01.695 --> 06:04.028
Oh, she already
texted me.

06:04.064 --> 06:06.097
"Saw your purse sitting
on the chair in the tent.

06:06.133 --> 06:09.667
I grabbed it. Go back to sleep
and stop worrying about me."

06:09.703 --> 06:11.069
She knows you well.

06:13.473 --> 06:16.674
Whoa, looks like I've
got eight voice mails.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.610
It's probably just
congratulations.

06:18.645 --> 06:20.378
Yeah, I don't think so.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.016
It sounds like something serious
has happened at the lab.

06:26.019 --> 06:27.919
They need me to come in.
Today?

06:35.395 --> 06:36.594
I got them, too.

06:36.630 --> 06:40.331
Oh, shoot, my ID's in my purse.

06:40.367 --> 06:41.599
I got it.

06:41.635 --> 06:44.335
Okay.

06:44.371 --> 06:46.738
Somebody talk to me.
What is happening?

06:46.773 --> 06:49.174
It appears Ms. Warren's
initial assessment is correct.

06:49.209 --> 06:50.542
Gunshot wound to the head.

06:50.577 --> 06:53.044
Okay, who's the victim?
We're not sure yet.

06:53.079 --> 06:54.223
So you called us in, and you
don't even have ID?

06:54.247 --> 06:55.814
This isn't exactly
a normal case.

06:55.849 --> 06:58.850
Seriously, guys, tell me,
what has gone wrong here?

06:59.786 --> 07:02.187
Everything.

